nodes.documentation:
@notice Challenge committee members during cooldown period.
     * @dev Must be called over Consensus to assert excluded member is
     a validator. Present a member that isn't present in the
     committee but should have been.
     Any excluded member invalidates the committee and member who
     initiated cooldown wrongly will be slashed.
     * @param _excludedMember Excluded member of the committee. Requires that
                       the specified account is not a member and
                       that its distance from the proposal is less than
                       furthest committee member distance.

nodes.documentation:
@notice Members can submit their sealed commit.
        The function transitions the committee to the reveal phase
        in either of the below conditions:
             - all members have submitted their sealed commits
             - commit timeout block height has been reached
     * @dev Function requires:
         - committee is in commit phase
         - only member can call
         - member can commit only once
     * @param _sealedCommit Sealed commit of a member. Non-zero value is
                     required.

activateCommittee().details: Function requires:         - only member can call         - committee is in cooling down status         - committee activation block height is reached

challengeCommittee(address).details: Must be called over Consensus to assert excluded member is     a validator. Present a member that isn't present in the     committee but should have been.     Any excluded member invalidates the committee and member who     initiated cooldown wrongly will be slashed.

params._excludedMember: Excluded member of the committee. Requires that                       the specified account is not a member and                       that its distance from the proposal is less than                       furthest committee member distance.

closeCommitPhase().details: Function requires:         - committee is in commit phase

cooldownCommittee().details: Function requires:         - only a member can call         - the committee is in an open state         - members' count in the committee is equal to the committee's           size

params._account: The account address to calculate distance from the                proposal.

enterCommittee(address,address).details: Function requires:         - only the consensus contract can call         - the committe's status is open         - the specified validator distance from the proposal is less           than the specified further member one.

params._furtherMember: Further member (compared with the validator)                      address. The specified address:                         - has been already entered
params._validator: Validator address to enter.                  The specified address:                     - is not 0                     - is not the member-sentinel                     - has not been already entered

revealCommit(bytes32,bytes32).details: Function requires:         - only member can call         - committee is in reveal phase         - member has submitted and has not reveal its commit yet         - position and salt must match with sealed commit

params._position: Position of the member's commit.                 Non-zero value is required.
params._salt: Salt of the member's submitted commit.

submitSealedCommit(bytes32).details: Function requires:         - committee is in commit phase         - only member can call         - member can commit only once

params._sealedCommit: Sealed commit of a member. Non-zero value is                     required.

activateCommittee().notice: Activates the committee after formation cooled down.        After activation commits can be submitted.

challengeCommittee(address).notice: Challenge committee members during cooldown period.

closeCommitPhase().notice: Allow explicit closure of commit phase to trigger        timeout condition.

cooldownCommittee().notice: Initiates cool down for the committee during which objections can        be raised for the members entered in the committee.

distanceToProposal(address).notice: Calculates a distance of the specified `_account` from the        `proposal`. The `_account` is shuffled/dislocated in the        hashed space before calculating a distande.

getMembers().notice: Returns an array of committee members.

revealCommit(bytes32,bytes32).notice: Members reveal their positions and salts.

shuffle(address).notice: Shuffles (dislocates) `_validator` in the hashed space using        `dislocation` member.

submitSealedCommit(bytes32).notice: Members can submit their sealed commit.        The function transitions the committee to the reveal phase        in either of the below conditions:             - all members have submitted their sealed commits             - commit timeout block height has been reached
